locality: Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Jabal Fartak between Haswayn and Al Ghaida, SW-facing slopes of the mountain and plateau with the radio station. Loamy pans with therophytic vegetation. Alt.: 550-950 m. 26.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 6902.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. along the track between Sayhut and Qeshn, 3 km N of the village Itáb. Silty-loamy pans in a gravelly wadi, with dense therophyte vegetation some weeks after heavy rains. Alt.: 50 m. 18.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein, S. O. Bahah, S. M. Bashmela & N. Kilian PH 6480.

Yemen: Gov. Abyan. Jabal Urays, middle Wadi Asurie, Sterculia africana zone. Relevé A50: NW-exposed slope (incl. 10-15°) with huge rocks, open woodland with scattered old Sterculia trees (trunk diam. 1.5-2 m), tree layer 2-10 m, shrub layer to 2 m tall. Alt.: 550-650 m. 17.3.2002, Leg.: P. Hein & H. Kürschner YP 1782.

Oman: Oman, Dhofar: plateau of the Jabal Samhan, near the radio station, alt. 1150-1250 m, 17°07'N, 54°43'E. Rocky hillslopes, monsoon affected Euphorbia balsamifera shrubland. Alt.: 1150-1250 m. 4.10.1998, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 5312a.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. coastal mountains between Al Faydami and Hawf, in bay 8 km W of Jadib, sandy-loamy soil with therophyte vegetation. Alt.: 2-5 m. 21.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein, S. O. Bahah, S. M. Bashmela & N. Kilian PH 6633.
